overviews.content: One Piece animation is based on the successful comic by Eiichiro Oda. The comic has sold more than 260 million copies. The success doesn't stop; the One Piece animation series is in its top 5 TV ratings for kids programs in Japan for past few years and the series' most recent feature film title "One Piece Film Z" which was released on December 2012 has gathered 5.6 million viewers so far. The success goes beyond borders; receives high popularity on animation at terrestrial channel in Taiwan, no.1 rating on animation at a DTT channel in France, received high popularity among age 3-13 on a terrestrial channel in Germany in year 2010. The animation series has been broadcasted in many parts of the world: USA, UK, Australia, France, Spain, Portugal, Germany, Italy, Greece, Turkey, Israel, South Korea, Taiwan, China, Hong Kong, Philippine, Thailand, Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, Ecuador, Nicaragua, Chile, Mexico, Brazil, and etc.

episodes.name: Luffy in an Emergency! The Living Place of the Strongest Shadow!
episodes.summary: Brook strikes the final blow in his battle with the spider monkey, Gecko Moria's plan is revealed. Luffy almost escapes.

episodes.name: The Warrior Called a Demon!! The Time of Oars's Resurrection
episodes.summary: Brook tells Franky and Robin the secret to slaying Zombies; Gecko Moria revels the terrifying monster that will be the recipient of Luffy's shadow.

episodes.name: Awakening After 500 Years!! Oars Revives!!
episodes.summary: After Luffy's shadow is forced into a monster, Nami is kidnapped and Usopp and Chopper try to rescue her.

episodes.name: Conviction Strong Enough to Beg for One's Life!! Brook Protects his Afro
episodes.summary: Gecko Moria's minions struggle with the burden of feeding a giant zombie.

episodes.name: A Man's Oath will Never Die! From Far Memories to the Waiting Friend
episodes.summary: Luffy, Zorro and Sanji discover that their shadows are missing; Franky relates to Brooks story about a promise he made to a very special whale.

episodes.name: We will Definately Meet Again! Brook and the Promise of the Cape
episodes.summary: Luffy and the Straw Hats flash back to the story of Laboon the abandoned whale; revelations about Brook's battle with the zombie samurai.

episodes.name: Food, Nami and Shadows!! Luffy's Angry Counterattack
episodes.summary: Luffy sets out to regain his shadow and convince the walking skeleton Brooks to become a member of his crew. Meanwhile, Sanji races to stop the Zombie leader from his plan to marry Nami.

episodes.name: Usopp the Strongest? Leave the Negatives to Me
episodes.summary: Usopp surprises everyone when he encounters the ghosts.

episodes.name: Sudden Death of the General Zombies!! Oars in an Adventurous Mood
episodes.summary: Brook is overmatched by the zombie samurai; Luffy prepares for his battle; Sanji interrupts the undead wedding.

episodes.name: Sanji, the Knight of Flames!! Kick Down the False Ceremony
episodes.summary: Luffy struggles to land a blow against Gecko Moria; Sanji's passionate attempt to defeat Nami's beastly abductor.

episodes.name: Invisibility Connection? Sanji's Stolen Dream
episodes.summary: Sanji takes a beating when his opponent suddenly turns invisible; Usopp battles with a zombie bear.

episodes.name: Saving Hero!! The Enemy is the Invincible Princess
episodes.summary: Usopp battles the ghost girl and tries to discover the secret of her sudden confidence.

episodes.name: Perona's Terror!! The U in Uso is the U in Usopp
episodes.summary: Usopp reaches deep into himself to help even the odds during his battle with the tricky Perona; Luffy finds during his battle that even laying a finger on Gecko Moria may be a major problem.

episodes.name: Slashes Dancing on the Roof!! Finale - Zoro vs. Ryuma
episodes.summary: Ryuma and Zoro duel in Hogback's laboratory while Franky guards the injured Brook. Neither opponent is able to gain over the other during the fight. Their attacks on each other quickly destroy the lab.

Defeat Absalom!! Nami's Lightning Attack of Friendship!
One Down!! Sure Kill Straw Hat Docking?
episodes.summary: Nami attempts to track down some missing treasure; Brook searches the kitchen for a mystery ingredient; a heroic team battle against Oars in a effort to topple him.

episodes.name: Soundless Invasion!! The Mysterious Visitor: Kuma the Tyrant
episodes.summary: Nami chases after Perona, who is fleeing from Thriller Bark; Kuma arrives and wrecks the place.

episodes.name: Oars + Moria - The Greatest Combination of Brains and Brawn
episodes.summary: Luffy discovers that he has been chasing Gekko's shadow wile the real Gekko escaped.

episodes.name: A Crazy Strategy to Turn the Tables - The Creation of Nightmare Luffy
episodes.summary: Oars manages to turn the tide of the battle by countering the Straw Hats; Nami arrives and joins the fight; Luffy meets some interesting individuals who might be of help.

episodes.name: The Straw Hat crew annihilated! Full-throttle Kage Kage abilities!
episodes.summary: Brook joins the fight; the Straw Hats try to hold off Oars and Moria until Luffy is able to return but they may not be able to.

episodes.name: The Battle for Superiority Starts! Luffy vs. Luffy
episodes.summary: While Oars and Moria is ruthlessly pummeling the Straw Hat pirates, Nightmare Luffy arrives to join the battle.

episodes.name: The Conclusion Arrives! Deliver the Finishing Blow
episodes.summary: After Luffy's shadow power disappears, he needs help from the rest of the Straw Hats to land the finishing blow in his battle against Oars.

episodes.name: The Bodies Vanish! The Morning Sun Pierces Through the Nightmare Island!
episodes.summary: Moria gobbles up every shadow in sight to power up for the final showdown with Luffy.

episodes.name: The Endless Crisis! Orders to Obliterate the Straw Hat Crew
episodes.summary: The battle between Luffy and Moria reaches it's end; Kuma causes panic on the island.

episodes.name: Kuma`s Nikyu Nikyu Abilities That Deflect Everything
episodes.summary: The World Government orders Kuma to obliterate every living being on the island.

episodes.name: My Companions' Pain is My Pain - Zoro Prepares to Die
episodes.summary: A heated confrontation occurs when Zoro and Sanji have to make a decision so they can save Luffy.

episodes.summary: Nami confronts Cracker and tries to use various tricks against him, but they prove ineffective and he overpowers her. However, Luffy regains his Haki and leaps back into the fray, taking Cracker by surprise with a Gear Second punch. In the Germa Kingdom, Sanji cannot continue fighting Niji due to the threat on Zeff, which allows Niji to pummel him. As his brothers stand over him, Sanji remembers his childhood in the Germa Kingdom. Judge had given him and his siblings superhuman abilities and had them train their skills, but Sanji continuously fell far behind his siblings' performances, causing him to be viciously bullied. Judge discovered that Sanji possessed no superhuman abilities after all, and he faked Sanji's death, locking his third son in a dungeon with an iron mask on to act like he never existed.

episodes.summary: After burying Luffy under a mountain of mochi, Katakuri believes he won and calls his chefs, who bring snacks for him to feast on. Katakuri makes a shrine where he can eat in private. Luffy breaks out of the mochi he was buried under and shattered the shrine, exposing Katakuri's face. Katakuri then executes the chefs before resuming his attempts to kill Luffy. After managing to land a hit on Katakuri, Luffy says that he figures out how to beat him and activates Gear Fourth.

episodes.summary: The banquet at Orochi's palace begins and Robin begins her mission. Shinobu, Nami, and Brook sneak into the palace as well. Meanwhile, in Udon prison, Kid explains to Luffy and Caribou about how he lost his arm. Back at the Flower Capital, two of the Flying Six, Page One and X Drake arrive to hunt down Sanji. In the seas surrounding Wano Country, the Big Mom Pirates draw closer.
